public int[] sortArrayByParityII(int[] nums) {
    int j = 1;
    for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i += 2) {
        if (nums[i] % 2 != 0) {
            while (nums[j] % 2 != 0) {
                j += 2;
            }
            int temp = nums[i];
            nums[i] = nums[j];
            nums[j] = temp;
        }
    }
    return nums;
}
```

    Iterate through the elements of the input array with a step of 2, starting at index 0 (even indices). If the current element is odd, find the nearest odd-indexed element that is even (variable j), and then swap the elements at these indices. This ensures that the even-indexed elements will be even and the odd indexed elements will be odd, satisfying the problem requirements. The time complexity of this algorithm is O(n).
